<TITLE> Geeteara blames fertiliser crisis on smuggling </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Chittagong, Nov 20 (bdnews24.com) -- Industry adviser Geeteara Safiya Choudhury Tuesday said that smuggling was the main reason for the fertilisr crisis in the country. She was speaking at a meeting with local administration officials on the fertiliser situation at the Chittagong Circuit House. "The crisis will diminish if smuggling is prevented," she said. The adviser asked law enforcers to take necessary steps to stop smuggling at all points including river and sea ports. She stressed essential steps to keep gas supply to Chittagong Urea Fertiliser Limited normal. "If smuggling and gas crisis are prevented, there won't be any fertilisr crisis in the country," Geeteara said. CUFL managing director Nazim Uddin said that fertiliser production had been hampered most of the year due to lack of gas. The adviser assured the CUFL officials that necessary steps would be taken to solve the gas problem. She claimed that there was no crisis of fertiliser in the country now. However, mismanagement in distribution would have to be removed, she added. The dealers have to work in collaboration with the local administration in this regard, Geeteara said. bdnews
